cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SI 

The paper discusses the use of machine learning models and neural networks for online learning and discovery of contextual changes in streaming data. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks for feature extraction and clustering suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.NE). Finally, the problem of identifying unknown contextual changes in streaming data can also be seen as a problem in signal processing (cs.SI).
